trans-unit.source: View the cost shares of all items in the parent item's product structure, their quantity and their cost shares specified in material, capacity, overhead, and total cost. Capacity and subcontractor costs are calculated as the costs related to produce all of the items in the parent item's product structure. Material cost is calculated as the cost of all items in the item's product structure. Capacity and subcontractor costs are the cost related to the parent item only.

trans-unit.source: Specifies a description for the item costing setup

If a part of the production order has been produced (Finished quantity < Quantity): the system calculates the consumption of materials and the times to be costed as a ratio between the 2 quantities (as in the calculation of the true WIP). If, on the other hand, the production order has been completed (Finished quantity >= Quantity), regardless of the status of the order, the system only costs the materials and actual times recorded (it does not recalculate anything). This logic also determines the calculation of the final amounts and the final unit costs present in the routing history.
trans-unit.target: Jos PO on osittain tuotettu (Valmis määrä <Määrä), järjestelmä laskee materiaalien kulutuksen ja kustannusten ajat näiden kahden määrän välisenä suhteena. Jos sen sijaan tilaus on valmistunut (Valmis määrä> = Määrä), itse tilauksen tilasta riippumatta järjestelmä maksaa vain kirjatut materiaalit ja todelliset ajat (ei suorita uudelleenlaskentaa). Tämä logiikka määrittää myös syklihistoriassa olevien lopullisten määrien ja lopullisten yksikkökustannusten laskemisen.
